      "title": "See also"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The probability mass function for the Log Series distribution is"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "formulas": [
            "P(k) = \\frac{-p^k}{k \\ln(1-p)},"
          ],
          "type": "math_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "where p = probability."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The log series distribution is frequently used to represent species\nrichness and occurrence, first proposed by Fisher, Corbet, and\nWilliams in 1943 [2].  It may also be used to model the numbers of\noccupants seen in cars [3]."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "1\n\nBuzas, Martin A.; Culver, Stephen J.,  Understanding regional\nspecies diversity through the log series distribution of\noccurrences: BIODIVERSITY RESEARCH Diversity & Distributions,\nVolume 5, Number 5, September 1999 , pp. 187-195(9).",
          "type": "raw_block"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "2\n\nFisher, R.A,, A.S. Corbet, and C.B. Williams. 1943. The\nrelation between the number of species and the number of\nindividuals in a random sample of an animal population.\nJournal of Animal Ecology, 12:42-58.",
          "type": "raw_block"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "3\n\nD. J. Hand, F. Daly, D. Lunn, E. Ostrowski, A Handbook of Small\nData Sets, CRC Press, 1994.",
          "type": "raw_block"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "4\n\nWikipedia, \"Logarithmic distribution\",\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logarithmic_distribution",
          "type": "raw_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "References"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Draw samples from the distribution:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "a = .6"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "rng = flops.random.default_rng()"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "s = rng.logseries(a, 10000)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "bins = flops.arange(-.5, max(s) + .5 )"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "count, bins, _ = plt.hist(s, bins=bins, label='Sample count')"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "#   plot against distribution"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "def logseries(k, p):"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": "...",
              "text": "return -p**k/(k*flops.log(1-p))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "centres = flops.arange(1, max(s) + 1)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.plot(centres, logseries(centres, a) * s.size, 'r', label='logseries PMF')"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.legend()"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.show()"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Examples"
    }
  ],
